Over the past few years, my prayers have changed incredibly. 

I used to pray as if there was a magic genie in the sky who choose when to grant my wishes. Begging for results and blessings I wanted.

But now I realize that better than any genie.. is a God who loves me unconditionally. 

Who has given me every tool I need to create the life I want.

He created ME. And with that knowledge, I know that I AM powerful. 

So in my prayers I just thank Him.

The words I speak are powerful. 

They create.

So I pray and speak the things I want created.

A few years ago I would have been asking for God to bless Knox’s body. To please heal Him. Please bless he gets better. Please don’t let this turn into something worse.

But now I just thanked God for the healing that was happening and the spirit was tangible. 

I felt the creator helping me create. A moment I’ll never forget 💛

I’m creating a life I LOVE. 

Life is not long enough to do anything that doesn’t bring you joy. 

I spent years being a people pleaser, a rule follower, asleep honestly to what really would light my soul on fire. 

Now today, I realize that I create my life. 

Even the hard things. 
Even the mundane. 
Even the trials and the joys and the triumphs. 

And if I start experiencing something I’m not enjoying, I learn and choose to move toward joy 💛

Today I LOVE the life I’m creating.

My prayer for all who feel the weight of life at this time. 

I pray that you can replace the fear and the worry with hope and joy. 

And over all, I pray that you can remember how very loved you are EXACTLY where you are right now. 

Through the trials, the loneliness, the doubt.. you are seen and LOVED immensely.

You matter.

You will make it through. 

You are not alone.

I’ve been trying to find the best way to help my kids learn the importance of helping around the home. 

We’ve gone through phases and charts and prizes and sticker charts.. and they all seem to work.. until they don’t 😅

We get lazy. We let things slide. We get out of the habit. And then somehow I’m the one left doing everything all over again! 

But I have to share with anyone who feels like they’re caught in this same cycle, what is absolutely working for us and STICKING. 

I don’t know if this is a good or bad thing 🤪 but my kids are extremely motivated by money! In the past, I never had cash on hand and the “I owe you’s” would always get lost or confused and my kids were never happy about it! 

So we found this app called @getbusykid and it’s changed our chores/responsibility game. 

Through the app, my kids can see all of their jobs and they get to check them off as they go! I put a price by each job (I literally do 5 cents) and they immediately see that added to their allowance for the week! They are STOKED about this and ask me all throughout the day to check off their items. 

My kids like checking things off lists as much as I do 🤣

Then every Friday, the money they earned gets transferred to their very own debit card 💪🏼 no more “I owe you’s”! 

But for real it’s been such a great addition to our home and I had to share 💛
